  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Direct non-invasive coronary imaging by computed tomography (CT) has the potential to improve
      the workup of patients with stable chest pain complaints. The objective of the study is to
      compare in a randomized fashion the effectiveness and efficiency of a CT angiographic driven
      workup of suspected coronary artery disease in comparison to the standard workup using stress
      testing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
